<theme id="thm205">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>8th note tied to group of one 8th and two 16th notes</title>
<tocimage>img205.png</tocimage>

<para>In this lesson a new rhythmic pattern is introduced:
One 8th note tied to group of one 8th and two 16th notes.
Note that this new pattern can be written in two different ways:</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <music_border>0</music_border>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <music>
        (time 2 4)(n a4 e g+)(n a4 e l g-)(n a4 e g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-)(barline double)
        (n a4 e)(n a4 q)(n a4 s g+)(n a4 s g-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>

<part>
<title>Listen and take notice of the differences</title>

<para>Listen to each measure and pay attention to the newly introduced patterns:</para>

<para><score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <score_type>short</score_type>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (time 2 4)(n a4 q)(n a4 e g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-)(barline)
        (n a4 e g+)(n a4 e g-)(n a4 e g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-)(barline)
        (n a4 e g+)(n a4 e l g-)(n a4 e g+)(n a4 s)(n a4 s g-)(barline end)
    </music>
</score></para>

</part>

<part>
<title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm205_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear and practise the
introduced rhythmic patterns.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm205_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

</theme>

